# Recovery Management CRM — Agent Build Prompt Library
### Paste-and-build prompts for coding agents, organized feature by feature

---

## How to use this document

1. **Paste Section 1 once**, at the start of your agent session (as the system prompt, `CLAUDE.md`, or project instructions). Every feature prompt after that assumes this context is already loaded — don't repeat it.
2. **Work top to bottom.** The order isn't arbitrary — later features depend on earlier ones (e.g., you can't build the case detail page's permission gating before CASL is wired up). Skipping ahead will produce rework.
3. **Each feature block** gives you: what it depends on, which libraries it touches, what must come from the backend/tenant config (vs. what's safe to hardcode), the actual prompt to paste, and acceptance criteria to verify before moving to the next one.
4. **Test the acceptance criteria before moving on.** An agent that "looks done" but fails silent state-persistence or permission edge cases will compound into a much bigger bug later.

