## 4. Phase 1 Feature Prompts (Months 1–4 — build these now, in order)

### Week 1

**Feature 0A — Repo scaffolding & tooling**
```
Scaffold the project: Vite + React 18 + TypeScript in strict mode. Configure ESLint
(no `any`, no unused vars, exhaustive-deps for hooks) and Prettier. Set up Tailwind
CSS with a config that reads from a single `src/design/tokens.ts` file (colors,
spacing scale, radius, font family) rather than Tailwind's defaults, so design tokens
and Tailwind never drift apart. Add Husky + lint-staged to block commits that fail
lint/type-check. Set up path aliases (`@/components`, `@/features`, `@/lib`, `@/design`).
Establish the folder structure: `src/app` (shell, routing), `src/features/*`
(feature-sliced, one folder per domain: cases, payments, dashboard, auth, admin),
`src/lib` (apiCaller, hooks, utils), `src/design` (tokens, theme).
```

**Feature 1 — `apiCaller.ts` core HTTP layer**
```
Build src/lib/apiCaller.ts: a single Axios instance, base URL from environment config.
Request interceptor: attach the in-memory access token (from useAuthStore) as
Authorization header, attach X-Tenant-Id from useTenantStore, attach a generated
X-Request-Id for tracing. Response interceptor: normalize all error responses into a
consistent shape { status, code, message, fields? }; on 401, attempt one silent token
refresh via the refresh endpoint (cookie-based, no body needed) and retry the original
request once — queue concurrent requests during the refresh so we don't fire N parallel
refresh calls; on repeated 401 after refresh, log the user out. On 403, do NOT show a
generic toast — return the error shape and let the calling feature decide (the UI
should have already prevented the action via PermissionGate, so a 403 reaching here is
either a race condition or a state the caller must handle explicitly). On 5xx, dispatch
a generic "Something went wrong, we've been notified" toast via notify.ts (build a
minimal stub for now) and log to console (Sentry wiring comes later).
Export typed resource wrapper modules (e.g. `casesApi.list()`, `casesApi.get(id)`) —
components must never import axios or apiCaller directly.
```

**Feature 2 — Auth shell (email/password)**
```
Build the login page and auth flow for email + password only (SSO comes in Week 13).
Form via React Hook Form + Zod (hardcode this one — login fields don't vary by
tenant). On submit, call the login endpoint via apiCaller, store the returned access
token in an in-memory Zustand slice (useAuthStore) — never localStorage or a
non-httpOnly cookie. The refresh token is set by the backend as an httpOnly cookie;
the frontend never touches it directly. Build a <ProtectedRoute> wrapper that
redirects unauthenticated users to /login and preserves the intended destination for
post-login redirect. Include: inline validation errors (never toasted), a loading
state on the submit button, a generic "Invalid email or password" error (never leak
which one was wrong), and a "Forgot password" link stub.
```

**Feature 3 — CI pipeline**
```
Set up a CI workflow (GitHub Actions or equivalent) that runs on every PR: type-check
(tsc --noEmit), lint, unit tests, and a build step, all required to pass before merge.
Add a bundle-size check step (even just a warning comment on the PR) so bloat is
visible early rather than discovered in Month 4's performance pass.
```

