## 7. Sequencing Notes

- Don't start Week 5 (case features) before Weeks 1–4 are genuinely done and tested — every later feature leans on the manifest/permission/URL-state/toast foundation, and retrofitting these patterns onto already-built screens is far more expensive than building them first.
- Features 0B and 0C (Dynamic Form Renderer, Workflow bindings) are the highest-leverage early investment given your "forms and decisions come from the backend" requirement — every subsequent form-heavy or workflow-heavy feature (18, 19, 39, 41, 42, 43) assumes they already exist.
- If you need to parallelize across multiple agents/developers, Weeks 1–4 are largely sequential (each depends on the last), but once the foundation is done, Weeks 5–12's features split reasonably cleanly by domain: one agent on case list/detail (13,16,17,20,21), another on dashboards/notifications (22,23,24,25), another on auth/security (31–34) — just make sure whoever builds 18/19 has 0B/0C finished first.
